The State files a Second Amended Information which adds count 3, misdemeanor PTC theft, contrary to Section 943.20(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
NO CONTEST pleas entered to counts 2 and 3 of the Second Amended Information, PTC criminal damage to property and PTC theft.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 1, PTC burglary.  Motion granted.
The Court comments and withheld sentence and places the defendant on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Continue with treatment as recommended and suggested by the agent;
3) No contact with Brandon Reinl;
4) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 2 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
5) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
